# Zod Schema Validation Guidelines

## General Rules

### Schema Definition
- Always use Zod for input validation
- Define reusable schemas as constants with descriptive names
- Use `z.object()` for structured data
- Follow TypeScript naming conventions for schema constants:
  ```typescript
  const userSchema = z.object({...})
  const productSchema = z.object({...})
  ```

### Type Inference
- Don't manually define types for validated data
- Use `z.infer<typeof schemaName>` if type is needed
- Example:
  ```typescript
  const productSchema = z.object({...})
  type Product = z.infer<typeof productSchema>
  ```

### Schema Composition
- Break down complex schemas into smaller, reusable parts
- Use composition over large single schemas
- Example:
  ```typescript
  const translationSchema = z.object({...})
  const metaSchema = z.object({...})
  const productSchema = z.object({
    ...translationSchema.shape,
    ...metaSchema.shape,
  })
  ```

### Validation Rules
- Use appropriate Zod methods for validation:
  - `.min()`, `.max()` for numbers/strings/arrays
  - `.email()` for email validation
  - `.url()` for URL validation
  - `.regex()` for pattern matching
  - `.nullable()` for null values
  - `.optional()` for optional fields
- Add meaningful error messages

### TRPC Integration
- Use Zod schemas directly in TRPC input validation
- Example from [apps/backend/src/modules/trpc/routers/admin/product.router.ts](mdc:apps/backend/src/modules/trpc/routers/admin/product.router.ts):
  ```typescript
  .input(z.object({
    locale: z.string().length(2),
    title: z.string(),
    content: z.string().optional()
  }))
  ```

## Best Practices

### Schema Organization
- Keep related schemas in the same file
- Export reusable schemas
- Place common schemas in shared locations
- Use descriptive names for schema constants

### Error Handling
- Provide custom error messages for better UX
- Use `.refine()` for complex validations
- Handle validation errors appropriately in TRPC

### Performance
- Reuse schema instances when possible
- Avoid unnecessary schema transformations
- Cache complex schema compositions

### Documentation
- Document complex validation rules
- Add comments for non-obvious validations
- Include examples for schema usage

